<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10561776>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Tachydromia bimaculata (Loew) (Canada, British Columbia; CNC). A. Male habitus, lateral view. B. Male head, anterior view. C. Male palpus, dorsal view. D. Female habitus, lateral view. E. Female head, anterior view. Abbreviation: plp—palpus." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10561776/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10561780>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Tachydromia bimaculata (Loew), male terminalia (Canada, British Columbia; CNC). A. Hypopygium, dorsal view. B. Right surstylus, lateral view. C. Left epandrial lamella and left surstylus, lateral view. Abbreviations: cerc—cercus; lft sur—left surstylus; rt sur—right surstylus. Scale bar is 0.1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10561780/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

